verbose_text: Chi-square test 's p-value < 0.001 suggested a statistically significant relationship between HI and NI antibody levels against each A/H1N1 in the same serum samples, although the correlation was rather low (Spearman rs = 0.32 [95% CI : 0.11-0.57], and rs = 0.29 [95% CI : 0.01-0.54], in case of H1N1/1999 and H1N1/2009pdm respectively).
